Darius Keaton, 63, former director ofSanta Fe International Corp, was sentenced to two months injail and fined 11,000 dlrs for trading the company's stock oninsider knowledge of its 1981 two-billion-dlr takeover.    Keaton, who was sentenced in Manhattan Federal Court,pleaded guilty to wire fraud and failing to report to theSecurities and Exchange Commission that he used his insideknowledge of a takeover by Kuwait Petroleum to buy shares ofSanta Fe's stock before the takeover was disclosed.     Keaton must also serve 1,000 hours of community serviceafter which he will be placed on probation for five years. Reuter&#3;